curl -d '{"name":"Peter", "age":5}' http://localhost:8080/user -H "Content-Type:application/json"
it doesn't work with Command propmpt, but it works with bash


to login into Cloud foundry from command prompt (doesn't seem to work in Bash)
cf login -a https://api.run.pivotal.io -skip-ssl-validation -u kharalanova@yahoo.com -p K@ty1068 -o kharalanova-org -s development

to publish on Cloud Foundry
cf push kp-spring-data-test-120219 -p target/spring-data-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar

application url:
https://kp-spring-data-test-120219.cfapps.io/

from https://console.run.pivotal.io/organizations/ca075c24-896a-4486-8d0a-b8aaebe3132e/spaces/2af82330-727d-4003-b8e4-e8c70f687211

to POST to the Cloud foundry application (but from Bash)
curl -d '{"name":"Peter", "age":5}' https://kp-spring-data-test-120219.cfapps.io/user -H "Content-Type:application/json"
